One thing I’ll say about having kids, you get to see their personalities evolve over time.  But certain things about them will always stay.

You’ll get to the point where even many years later, you will be able to predict their behaviors even into their teen years (it starts getting more difficult at that point).

My kids are all teens now except for my 6 year old.  But I can tell you that they all used to be amazed that I would know who was coming down the stairs by their walk, or what they were about to eat, or all kinds of stuff.  To them, you seem psychic.  But really it’s just that you’ve known them since they were tiny and you know infinitely mire about them than they’ll ever know about you.

It’s a very cool and surreal experience.
